spans.text: No more the Rose nor Hyacinth were seen , Nor yellow Cowslip on the tufted Green : But the rude Thistle reared its hoary Crown , And the ripe Nettle showed an irksome Brown
Parched were those Lips whence Music
Yet thrice to raise her feeble Voice she tried , Thrice on her Tongue the fainting Numbers died
I see , Who droop their Heads as though they wept for me
Which Colinetta must behold no more
Where , when an Infant , I was wont to stray , And gather Kingcups at the closing Day
a cheerful Lay , While the glad Goldfinch listened on the Spray : Lured by my Song each jolly Swain drew near , And rosy Virgins thronged around to hear

my Dog to hunt their Flocks away , That mine might graze upon the vacant Lay
